In Spain ,

What they call High School in Spain would be the " Bachillerato " , which are grades 11 and 12 .

Children who complete vocational high school can then enter a technological university . Complete high school is like that of American high schools , in that it has grades seven to grade

highs and beefed-up bass not_only produces greater fidelity , but it eliminates listener fatigue . A contributing factor is the perspective , the uniform aesthetic distance which is maintained .
